==English==
===Etymology===
From the {{Gr.}} meaning "protectress," related to ''heros'', (defender).

===Proper Noun===
'''Hera'''
{{wikipedia}}
#{{greekmyth}}: The queen of the gods, and goddess of [[marriage]] and [[birth]]; daughter of [[Cronus]] and [[Rhea]], sister and wife of [[Zeus]], mother of [[Hephaestus]], [[Ares]], and [[Hebe]]

